  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The objective of this report is to describe a new surgical technique for the treatment of
      bony mallet finger which involves the application of both Kirschner wire and pull-out wire
      fixation. It is believed to decrease the risk of the complications.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      From May 2003 to December 2008, we used Kirschner wire and pull-out wire fixation to carry
      out 54 closed bony mallet finger in 54 patients. The bony mallet finger was applicated both
      Kirschner wire and pull-out wire fixation.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
